Type: Skill
Name: bio-single-cell-tcr-startrac-r
Description: STARTRAC (Single T-cell Analysis by Rna-seq and Tcr TRACking) for T cell dynamics analysis. Quantifies T cell clonotype expansion, migration between tissues, and state transitions.
Version: 1.0.0
Author: NanoResearch Skills
License: MIT
Language: R

Dependencies:
  - Startrac (>= 0.1.0)
  - Seurat (>= 4.0)
  - data.table
  - plyr
  - doParallel
  - ggplot2
  - ComplexHeatmap
  - RColorBrewer
  - circlize
  - ggpubr
  - dplyr
  - tidyr
  - cowplot

Key Functions:
  - prepare_startrac_input(): Convert Seurat to STARTRAC format
  - run_startrac(): Main analysis pipeline
  - run_startrac_by_patient(): Per-patient analysis
  - plot_startrac_results(): Comprehensive visualization
  - export_startrac_results(): Export to CSV/RDS/Excel

Input Format:
  Required columns: Cell_Name, clone.id, patient, majorCluster, loc

Output Indices:
  - expa: Clonal expansion index
  - migr: Tissue migration index
  - tran: Phenotypic transition index
